msgid ""
"Documentation of Spack, a flexible package manager for high-performance "
"computing, designed to support multiple versions and configurations of "
"software on a wide variety of platforms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:16
msgid "Spack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../index.rst:18
msgid ""
"Spack is a package management tool designed to support multiple versions and "
"configurations of software on a wide variety of platforms and environments. "
"It was designed for large supercomputing centers, where many users and "
"application teams share common installations of software on clusters with "
"exotic architectures, using libraries that do not have a standard ABI. Spack "
"is non-destructive: installing a new version does not break existing "
"installations, so many configurations can coexist on the same system."
msgstr ""
"Spack 是一款軟體包管理工具，旨在支援多種平台與環境下的多個軟體版本及組態。它"
"專為大型超級電腦中心設計，在這些中心裡，許多使用者與應用程式團隊會在具有特殊"
"架構的叢集上共享軟體安裝，且使用的函式庫通常不具備標準 ABI。Spack 具有非破壞"
"性：安裝新版本不會損壞現有的安裝，因此多種組態可以共存於同一個系統中。"

#: ../../../index.rst:22
msgid ""
"Most importantly, Spack is *simple*. It offers a simple *spec* syntax so "
"that users can specify versions and configuration options concisely. Spack "
"is also simple for package authors: package files are written in pure "
"Python, and specs allow package authors to maintain a single file for many "
"different builds of the same package."
msgstr ""
"最重要的是，Spack 非常 *簡單* 。它提供了一種簡單的規格（spec）語法，讓使用者"
"能簡潔地指定版本與組態選項。對於軟體包作者而言，Spack 同樣簡單：軟體包檔案是"
"以純 Python 編寫，且規格語法允許作者僅需維護單一檔案，即可對應同一個軟體包的"
"多種不同建置版本。"

